   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LESSON FOUR THE PRACTICE OF</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE LORD'S TABLE MEETING 1 Scripture Reading: 1 Cor 11:23-25 OUTLINE Remembering the Lord 1 Cor 11:24-25: By praising instead of by praying: Not to ask the Lord to do things for us.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>But to bless the Lord with well-speaking concerning His person and work Rev 5:13.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Addressing praise to the Lord Jesus Christ, the Son of God: Realizing the economy of the Divine Trinity Matt 28:19b; 2 Cor 13:14.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Learning to differentiate the Lord's names from the Father's names see hymns 65-80, Hymns .</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Calling hymns: Learning to know the hymns: In their categories.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>In their contents.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>In their focus.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>In their sensation and taste.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Learning to apply the hymns at the appropriate time: To start a section of the meeting.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>To strengthen and enrich the started section.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>To prolong and uplift the same section.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>To follow the atmosphere of the meeting.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Distributing the bread and the cup: Neither too early nor too late.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>When the remembrance of the Lord reaches the high tide.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Better with some thanks given to the Lord Luke 22:19a.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Focus: The proper remembrance of the Lord depends upon our proper practice.</S>
   </TEXT>
